# Animation Guidelines

## Use Framer Motion for Animations

### Standard Transitions
```typescript
// Smooth spring for UI elements
const springTransition = { 
  type: "spring", 
  stiffness: 300, 
  damping: 20 
};

// Bouncy for playful elements
const bounceTransition = { 
  type: "spring", 
  stiffness: 500, 
  damping: 15 
};

// Quick for feedback
const quickTransition = { 
  duration: 0.2 
};
```

### Common Animation Patterns

```tsx
// Fade in
<motion.div
  initial={{ opacity: 0 }}
  animate={{ opacity: 1 }}
  transition={{ duration: 0.3 }}
/>

// Scale up entrance
<motion.div
  initial={{ scale: 0.8, opacity: 0 }}
  animate={{ scale: 1, opacity: 1 }}
  transition={springTransition}
/>

// Slide from right (RTL-aware)
<motion.div
  initial={{ x: -50, opacity: 0 }}
  animate={{ x: 0, opacity: 1 }}
/>

// Button press effect
<motion.button
  whileHover={{ scale: 1.05 }}
  whileTap={{ scale: 0.95 }}
/>

// Bounce loop (for attention)
<motion.div
  animate={{ y: [0, -10, 0] }}
  transition={{ repeat: Infinity, duration: 0.6 }}
/>

// Shake for wrong answer
<motion.div
  animate={{ x: [0, -10, 10, -10, 10, 0] }}
  transition={{ duration: 0.4 }}
/>

// Confetti burst for correct
<motion.div
  initial={{ scale: 0, rotate: 0 }}
  animate={{ scale: 1, rotate: 360 }}
  transition={{ type: "spring", stiffness: 200 }}
/>
```

### Page Transitions
```tsx
// Wrap pages with AnimatePresence
<AnimatePresence mode="wait">
  <motion.div
    key={pageKey}
    initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 20 }}
    animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
    exit={{ opacity: 0, y: -20 }}
    transition={{ duration: 0.3 }}
  >
    {children}
  </motion.div>
</AnimatePresence>
```

### Staggered Children
```tsx
// Container with stagger
<motion.ul
  variants={{
    visible: { transition: { staggerChildren: 0.1 } }
  }}
  initial="hidden"
  animate="visible"
>
  {items.map(item => (
    <motion.li
      key={item.id}
      variants={{
        hidden: { opacity: 0, y: 20 },
        visible: { opacity: 1, y: 0 }
      }}
    />
  ))}
</motion.ul>
```

## Performance Tips
- Use `transform` and `opacity` for smooth 60fps
- Avoid animating `width`, `height`, `top`, `left`
- Use `layoutId` for shared element transitions
- Add `will-change` for complex animations
